  "root_text": {
    "sn56.96-101:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 56.96–101 ",
    "sn56.96-101:0.2": "10. Catutthaāmakadhaññapeyyālavagga ",
    "sn56.96-101:0.3": "Chedanādisutta ",
    "sn56.96-101:1.1": "… “Evameva kho, bhikkhave, appakā te sattā ye chedanavadhabandhanaviparāmosaālopasahasākārā paṭiviratā; atha kho eteva bahutarā sattā ye chedanavadhabandhanaviparāmosaālopasahasākārā appaṭiviratā. ",
    "sn56.96-101:1.2": "Taṁ kissa hetu? ",
    "sn56.96-101:1.3": "Adiṭṭhattā bhikkhave, catunnaṁ ariyasaccānaṁ. ",
    "sn56.96-101:1.4": "Katamesaṁ catunnaṁ? ",
    "sn56.96-101:1.5": "Dukkhassa ariyasaccassa …pe… dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya ariyasaccassa. ",
    "sn56.96-101:2.1": "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṁ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo …pe… ‘ayaṁ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti. ",
    "sn56.96-101:2.2": "Ekādasamaṁ. ",
    "sn56.96-101:2.3": "Catutthaāmakadhaññapeyyālavaggo dasamo. ",
    "sn56.96-101:3.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "sn56.96-101:3.1": "Khettaṁ kāyaṁ dūteyyañca, ",
    "sn56.96-101:3.2": "tulākūṭaṁ ukkoṭanaṁ; ",
    "sn56.96-101:3.3": "Chedanaṁ vadhabandhanaṁ, ",
    "sn56.96-101:3.4": "viparālopaṁ sāhasanti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn56.96-101:0.1": "Linked Discourses 56.96–101 ",
    "sn56.96-101:0.2": "10. Abbreviated Texts on Raw Grain ",
    "sn56.96-101:0.3": "Mutilation, Etc. ",
    "sn56.96-101:1.1": "“… the sentient beings who refrain from mutilation, murder, abduction, banditry, plunder, and violence are few, while those who don’t refrain are many. ",
    "sn56.96-101:1.2": "Why is that? ",
    "sn56.96-101:1.3": "It’s because they haven’t seen the four noble truths. ",
    "sn56.96-101:1.4": "What four? ",
    "sn56.96-101:1.5": "The noble truths of suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path. ",
    "sn56.96-101:2.1": "That’s why you should practice meditation …” ",
